Interface MenuItem

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MenuItemImpl, MenuItemTblImpl.DbMenuItem
    public interface MenuItem
    An interface to keep track of menu items and their ingredients.

      • checkSufficientIngredients

        boolean checkSufficientIngredients​(Business toCheck)
        Checks whether the given Business has enough ingredients to create the MenuItem. Note that if the Business does not have an Ingredient in its map, this is considered to be insufficient ingredients. Returns true if there are sufficient ingredients, false otherwise.
        Parameters:
        toCheck - The Business to check against
        Returns:
        A boolean, true if sufficient, false otherwise

      • calculateNumServings

        int calculateNumServings​(Business toCheck)
        Checks how many servings of the MenuItem the Business can create. Note that if the Business does not have an Ingredient in its map, this is considered to be zero servings possible.
        Parameters:
        toCheck - The Business to check against
        Returns:
        An int amount of servings possible
